<p><b>  Information from the Government 
</b></p>
<p>61. The Government transmitted three communications dated 22 February, 14 April and 
4 November 2010. In the first communication, the Government provided information on 
seven outstanding cases. Based on this information, the Working Group decided at its 
ninety-second session to apply the six-month rule to one case. For the other six cases, the 
information provided did not lead to clarification. The second and third communications 
could not be translated in time for inclusion in the present report. 
</p>
