<p><b>  Observations  
</b></p>
<p>81. The Working Group reminds the Government of its obligations under the 
Declaration to conduct thorough and impartial investigations &#8220;for as long as the fate of the 
victim of enforced disappearance remains unclarified&#8221; (art. 13.6) and to ensure that statutes 
of limitations, where they exist, relating to acts of enforced disappearance are substantial 
and commensurate with the extreme seriousness of the offence (art. 17.3). 
</p>
<p>82. The Working Group calls upon the Government to sign and ratify the International 
Convention for the Protection of All Persons from Enforced Disappearance and accept the 
competence of the Committee under articles 31 and 32. </p>


